) are described. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[151,396,545,570]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[151,396,545,570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Leschenaultia bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded for the first time from 
<collectingRegion box="[786,1014,545,570]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Toma, 2019" authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[1025,1245,545,570]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liriai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1025,1245,545,570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Leschenaultia liriai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1252,1316,545,570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1252,1316,545,570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
represents the first record of this genus from 
<collectingRegion box="[534,647,580,605]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="105" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
Within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[283,440,616,641]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[283,440,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Leschenaultia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, abdominal setae arrangements have been shown to be constant within different species and can be used for species recognition. However, their use is limited due to the recurrence of similar patterns between some species and because of intraspecific variation in a few species. Abdominal chaetotaxy, along with shape of cerci and surstyli, have taxonomic value in the recognition of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[952,1109,723,748]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[952,1109,723,748]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Leschenaultia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="Toma, R. &amp; Guimaraes, J. H." pageId="2" pageNumber="105" pagination="33 - 70" refId="ref10627" refString="Toma, R. &amp; Guimaraes, J. H. (2002) Estudo taxonomico de Leschenaultia Robineau-Desvoidy (Diptera, Tachinidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 46, 33 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262002000100006" type="journal article" year="2002">Toma &amp; Guimarães 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Toma, R." box="[222,354,760,784]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" pagination="353 - 354" refId="ref10578" refString="Toma, R. (2008) A new species of Leschenaultia Robineau-Desvoidy (Diptera, Tachinidae) from Venezuela and new geographical records. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 52, 353 - 354. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262008000300007" type="journal article" year="2008">Toma 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Other structures of the male terminalia such as hypandrial arms, pregonite and postgonite have taxonomic importance for recognition of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
Three of the new species described here, 
<taxonomicName authority="Toma, 2019" authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[667,794,830,855]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belkysae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[667,794,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. belkysae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[802,866,830,855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[802,866,830,855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Toma, 2019" authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[881,1003,831,855]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frangeri" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[881,1003,831,855]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. frangeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1011,1075,830,855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1011,1075,830,855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Toma, 2019" authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[1131,1217,830,855]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liriai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1131,1217,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. liriai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1225,1290,830,855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1225,1290,830,855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, resemble 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toma &amp; Guimaraes" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brooksi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. brooksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They are very similar in their external morphology, characterized by syntergite 1+2 and tergite 3 with a few very short median marginal setae almost undifferentiated from the ground setulae and tergites 3 and 4 without discal setae. These species can be distinguished from each other mainly by differences in the cercus in profile, especially curvatures of its anterior and posterior portions as well as differences in width and the extent of tapering of the apical portion, as mentioned in the Recognition section under each species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Toma, R. &amp; Guimaraes, J. H." box="[1140,1433,1009,1034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" pagination="33 - 70" refId="ref10627" refString="Toma, R. &amp; Guimaraes, J. H. (2002) Estudo taxonomico de Leschenaultia Robineau-Desvoidy (Diptera, Tachinidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 46, 33 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262002000100006" type="journal article" year="2002">Toma &amp; Guimarães 2002</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 52 for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toma &amp; Guimaraes" authorityYear="2002" box="[273,386,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brooksi">
<emphasis box="[273,386,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. brooksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The other two new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Toma, 2019" authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[726,849,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andarae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[726,849,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. andarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[857,921,1045,1070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[857,921,1045,1070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Toma, 2019" authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[977,1132,1046,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marjorieae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[977,1132,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. marjorieae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1139,1203,1045,1070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1139,1203,1045,1070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, differ from the first three by having syntergite 1+2 and tergite 3 with a few pairs of short median marginal setae differentiated from the ground setulae and tergites 3 and 4 with discal setae. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[750,1008,1116,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andarae">
<emphasis box="[750,1008,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Leschenaultia andarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toma &amp; Guimaraes" authorityYear="2002" box="[1063,1157,1116,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bigoti">
<emphasis box="[1063,1157,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. bigoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the only two species in this genus with grayish-yellow pruinosity on the head and can be distinguished from each other mainly by the length of the first flagellomere and differences in the male terminalia. Among the Brazilian species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Toma, 2019" authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[1281,1436,1189,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marjorieae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1281,1436,1189,1212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. marjorieae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,219,1223,1248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,219,1223,1248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
shares with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[373,480,1223,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cilipes">
<emphasis box="[373,480,1223,1248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. cilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toma &amp; Guimaraes" authorityYear="2002" box="[544,662,1225,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="currani">
<emphasis box="[544,662,1225,1248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. currani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the following combination of characteristics: head gray pruinose, syntergite 1+2 and tergite 3 with a few pairs of short median marginal setae, and tergites 3 and 4 with a group of short but well-visible discal setae. These species show little difference in abdominal chaetotaxy and are hardly separated from each other by external morphology, but they can be well separated by the differences in the male terminalia listed in the Recognition section of 
<taxonomicName authority="Toma, 2019" authorityName="Toma" authorityYear="2019" box="[669,823,1368,1391]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Leschenaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marjorieae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[669,823,1368,1391]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">L. marjorieae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[830,894,1366,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[830,894,1366,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and as presented in the key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
